ary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating JIT and CI coverage**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking about how JIT usually inlines but not at this early stage. In terms of CI coverage, it uses an agent or interpreter. There seems to be a potential issue with writing to a static final field through Unsafe, which could mess up the `Field.class` object in `inheritableThreadLocals`. Good that the field is declared final. There's also a native concern with Finalizer.startFinalizer, which has a reflection Constructor.newInstance using bigThreadConstructor. If the class initializes at image build, the constructor field might miss some metadata. My previous test passed, but do I need to add `@SuppressWarnings(\\\\\\\"removal\\\\\\\")`?\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_BbHxKUBB8B0aJhvwcZuCw9Cd|fc_0bc0152183978deb0169f9567bd7b88197a9b44d84d4663758\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find . -name '*checkstyle*' -type f -o -name 'checkstyle.xml'\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 1291, \"output\": 724, \"cacheRead\": 38400, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 40415, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777948270832, \"responseId\": \"resp_0bc0152183978deb0169f9566f6dac8197980cbab93aba2e5c\"}}\n4094:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating JIT and CI coverage**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how JIT usually inlines but not at this early stage. In terms of CI coverage, it uses an agent or interpreter. There seems to be a potential issue with writing to a static final field through Unsafe, which could mess up the `Field.class` object in `inheritableThreadLocals`. Good that the field is declared final. There's also a native concern with Finalizer.startFinalizer, which has a reflection Constructor.newI